verbs.description: [ARGM-ADV: For many high - profile athletes] , [ARG1: a visit to the White House after a championship season] [V: is] [ARGM-NEG: no longer] [ARG2: just a prestigious photo op] . Under the Trump administration , every crowning of a champion leads to a media debate about what teams or players should do . Does a visit to take a picture with President Donald Trump signal an endorsement of all he 's said and done ? Should players attempt to use that time to deliver a political message to the president ? Is skipping the visit altogether an effective protest ? So players are repeatedly asked their thoughts on the subject , and the media compare pictures of Trump 's crowd versus Obama 's crowd , and people forget that the whole thing was only ever supposed to be a fun experience for athletes , many of whom would never otherwise have an opportunity to go to the White House , or for presidents who are big sports fans .
